Hi Rick -

What you want to do is no problem. Simply define ionized species as  
containing the special element &quot;E&quot;.  Foe example, K+ would contain  
one atom of  potassium, and -1 atoms of &quot;E&quot;.
Cantera comes with some thermo files, at least one of which has the  
thermo properties for gaseous electrons.   As far as equilibrium  
(Saha equation), the solvers handle charged species fine, and the  
results would be the same as computed from the Saha equation.  Take a  
look at the Python demo &quot;multiphase_plasma.py&quot; in the demos/Python/ 
equilibrium folder. It has both multiple condensed phases and ionized  
gaseous species.

Dave



